🔧 Step: Build Aggregated Average Prices for Outlier Detection
	•	Goal: consolidate Ist-normalized prices from multiple CSVs into one lookup table (JSON).
	•	Input: 4 extracted CSVs:
	•	pc_hc_l_ist_normalized_prices.csv
	•	pc_hc_nl_ist_normalized_prices.csv
	•	pc_sc_l_ist_normalized_prices.csv
	•	pc_sc_nl_ist_normalized_prices.csv
	•	Output: ist_avg_prices.json containing:

{
  "Ber Rune": 9.75,
  "Cham Rune": 3.35,
  "Jah Rune": 10.4,
  ...
}

	•	Process:
1️⃣ Read each CSV.
2️⃣ Skip “Ist Rune” rows.
3️⃣ Weight each price by trade count.
4️⃣ Merge all data across servers.
5️⃣ Compute weighted average per rune.
6️⃣ Output as JSON.
	•	Purpose:
This file is used during anomaly inspection to flag trades where:

trade_price > 2 * avg_price   OR   trade_price < 0.5 * avg_price


⸻

✅ This step allows outlier detection to be adaptive across all rune price levels, rather than hard-coding thresholds.

